Ragtime is a 1981 American drama film , directed by Milo≈° Forman , based on 1975 historical novel Ragtime by E. L. Doctorow .
The action takes place in and around New York City , New Rochelle , and Atlantic City early in the 1900s , including fictionalized references to actual people and events of the time .
The film features the final film appearances of James Cagney and Pat O'Brien ; early appearances , in small parts , by Samuel L. Jackson , Jeff Daniels , Fran Drescher , Ethan Phillips and John Ratzenberger ; and an uncredited appearance from Jack Nicholson .
The music score was composed by Randy Newman .
The film was nominated for eight Oscars .